30/06/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul warned on Sunday (29 June) that if the EU does not begin accession negotiations with Turkey by the end of 2004, the country might lose its enthusiasm for integration. 
In a television interview, Gul said postponed negotiations might also affect enthusiasm among EU members.
In other news, Turkish police arrested 51 people Sunday in three separate demonstrations against the country's high-security prison system. 
Eighteen were arrested in Samsun and another 23 in Antakya. 
Ten more were arrested while demonstrating in front of Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan's residence. 
(Anadolu Agency, AFP, TRT 2 - 29/06/03)
